            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="nar.03457.001.jpg" type="verso"/>
           
            <ab>Nov. 9, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. Wm. W. Belknap,</ab>
            <ab>Secretary of War.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your communication of the 7th instant, transmitting papers relating to an attempt of S. G. Burbridge, to perpetrate a fraud upon the Quartermaster's Department by making out a false claim, <hi rend="underline">et</hi> <hi rend="underline">cet</hi>.,&#8212;and to inform you that the papers have been transmitted to the District Attorney of Kentucky for proper action.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c.</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman, Attorney General.</ab>
            
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">S. G. Burbridge</note>
            
            
            
